<subSubSection id="1EDB6615B578680A6D0FF6851C5D4390" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C92BD39370126044E65BC4C1570C67D6" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName id="0F53ECB9DDD8B884B7D33D44905667B7" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Opisthius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Opisthius</taxonomicName>
Kirby, 1837: 60. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="F2E7B3272D6A54663C41CC0430B41A83" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Opisthius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="richardsoni">
<emphasis id="027F3D06A846693B9CFDF2A971958E31" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Opisthius richardsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kirby, 1837 by monotypy. Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis id="AA01EE2DC806D0E7432AED5743720F37" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">opisthen</emphasis>
(behind) or 
<emphasis id="831FE24007920CFC96873EA557D72530" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">opisthios</emphasis>
(hinder) [masculine]. Bousquet and Smetana (1996: 218) suggested that the name possibly reflect 
<normalizedToken id="991F9CAA8FBEA15C7B02AEC849C6352E" originalValue="Kirby’s">Kirby's</normalizedToken>
assignment of 
<taxonomicName id="7F065FADBA4A847DD7617E5EE39F89DE" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Opisthius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="138497D1DF5BAAF424933B428B3D1D7B" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Opisthius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to follow 
<taxonomicName id="7BDAF0D4069A4DD70456B8071711A336" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Elaphrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4AD21563CF0BF223DE2C74DE2101695F" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Elaphrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1306F6F6457EA8A0152BD786E1777FEE" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="8542510AEE29D4C95BB7C4E06F5CBDA9" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1DFB0E20149F7282647A559151EC1BF" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">One North American species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="76056FEF5701CB5AD5608AC90D4AB73E" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="identification">
<paragraph id="201A46270A5BA809663E770A143C1EEF" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="324F4D0E5667199D993C18E7940F72F5" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
